2
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,780
Mr. Dufresne, describe...

3
00:02:15,980 --> 00:02:20,140
...the confrontation you had with
your wife the night she was murdered.

4
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:26,220
It was very bitter.

5
00:02:26,540 --> 00:02:30,660
She said she was glad I knew,
that she hated all the sneaking around.

6
00:02:32,180 --> 00:02:35,500
And she said that she wanted
a divorce in Reno.

7
00:02:35,740 --> 00:02:39,260
-What was your response?
-I told her I would not grant one.

8
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:42,500
"I'll see you in hell
before I see you in Reno."

9
00:02:42,660 --> 00:02:45,900
Those were your words,
according to your neighbors.

10
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,460
If they say so.

11
00:02:48,980 --> 00:02:51,380
I really don't remember.
I was upset.

12
00:02:51,660 --> 00:02:53,980
What happened after you argued
with your wife?

13
00:02:55,100 --> 00:02:56,780
She packed a bag.

14
00:02:57,900 --> 00:03:00,940
She packed a bag to go
and stay with Mr. Quentin.

15
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:05,500
Glenn Quentin, golf pro
at the Snowden Hills Country Club...

16
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:08,700
...whom you had discovered
was your wife 's lover.

17
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,060
Did you follow her?

18
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:15,380
I went to a few bars first.

19
00:03:15,540 --> 00:03:19,740
Later, I drove to his house
to confront them. They weren't home.

20
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:21,780
I parked in the turnout...

21
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:23,380
...and waited.

22
00:03:23,580 --> 00:03:25,180
With what intention?

23
00:03:25,740 --> 00:03:27,140
I'm not sure.

24
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:29,620
I was confused...

25
00:03:29,820 --> 00:03:30,820
...drunk.

26
00:03:32,260 --> 00:03:33,540
I think...

27
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:35,740
...mostly I wanted to scare them.

28
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:39,220
When they arrived, you went up
to the house and murdered them.

29
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:41,460
I was sobering up.

30
00:03:41,620 --> 00:03:45,140
I got back in the car
and I drove home to sleep it off.

31
00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:48,180
Along the way, I threw my gun
into the Royal River.

32
00:03:48,380 --> 00:03:50,300
I've been very clear on this point.

33
00:03:50,540 --> 00:03:54,420
I get hazy where the cleaning woman
shows up the following morning...

34
00:03:54,620 --> 00:03:57,100
...and finds your wife in bed
with her lover...

35
00:03:57,340 --> 00:03:59,340
...riddled with .38-caliber bullets.

36
00:04:00,620 --> 00:04:04,660
Does that strike you as a
fantastic coincidence, or is it just me?

37
00:04:05,540 --> 00:04:06,500
Yes, it does.

38
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:09,700
Yet you still maintain
you threw your gun into the river...

39
00:04:09,900 --> 00:04:11,900
...before the murders took place.

40
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:14,260
That's very convenient.

41
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,020
It's the truth.

42
00:04:16,380 --> 00:04:20,780
The police dragged that river for
three days, and nary a gun was found...

43
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:24,860
...so no comparison could be made
between your gun and the bullets...

44
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:28,420
...taken from the bloodstained corpses
of the victims.

45
00:04:29,020 --> 00:04:31,300
And that also...

46
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:35,060
...is very convenient.
Isn't it, Mr. Dufresne?

47
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,340
Since I am innocent of this crime...

48
00:04:38,540 --> 00:04:42,980
...I find it decidedly inconvenient
that the gun was never found.

49
00:05:00,140 --> 00:05:03,340
Ladies and gentlemen, you've heard
all the evidence.

50
00:05:03,540 --> 00:05:07,220
We have the accused at the scene
of the crime. We have footprints.

51
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:10,180
Bullets on the ground
bearing his fingerprints.

52
00:05:10,380 --> 00:05:13,220
A broken bourbon bottle,
likewise with fingerprints.

53
00:05:13,380 --> 00:05:14,900
And most of all...

54
00:05:15,100 --> 00:05:18,060
...we have a beautiful young woman
and her lover...

55
00:05:18,220 --> 00:05:20,180
...lying dead in each other's arms.

56
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,820
They had sinned.

57
00:05:24,980 --> 00:05:27,420
But was their crime so great...

58
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,780
...as to merit a death sentence?

59
00:05:29,980 --> 00:05:32,180
