more faith in me than that.

1040
01:18:46,960 --> 01:18:49,840
I know you're good,
but all that paper leaves a trail.

1041
01:18:50,040 --> 01:18:53,280
Now anybody gets curious,
FBI, IRS...

1042
01:18:53,520 --> 01:18:54,440
...whatever.

1043
01:18:54,880 --> 01:18:56,120
It'll lead to somebody.

1044
01:18:56,320 --> 01:19:00,040
Sure it is, but not to me,
and certainly not to the warden.

1045
01:19:04,240 --> 01:19:05,200
All right, who?

1046
01:19:05,360 --> 01:19:06,920
Randall Stevens.

1047
01:19:07,400 --> 01:19:08,320
Who?

1048
01:19:08,520 --> 01:19:10,440
The "silent" silent partner.

1049
01:19:10,640 --> 01:19:13,560
He's the guilty one,
the man with the bank accounts.

1050
01:19:13,760 --> 01:19:15,840
It's where the filtering
process starts.

1051
01:19:16,040 --> 01:19:18,760
They trace anything,
it'll just lead to him.

1052
01:19:19,360 --> 01:19:20,520
But who is he?

1053
01:19:20,720 --> 01:19:24,520
He's a phantom, an apparition.
Second cousin to Harvey the Rabbit.

1054
01:19:25,600 --> 01:19:26,720
I conjured him...

1055
01:19:26,880 --> 01:19:28,240
...out of thin air.

1056
01:19:29,000 --> 01:19:31,600
He doesn't exist, except on paper.

1057
01:19:34,560 --> 01:19:36,840
You can't just make a person up.

1058
01:19:37,040 --> 01:19:39,960
Sure you can,
if you know how the system works.

1059
01:19:40,480 --> 01:19:43,200
It's amazing what you
can accomplish by mail.

1060
01:19:43,520 --> 01:19:46,040
Mr. Stevens has a birth certificate...

1061
01:19:46,240 --> 01:19:48,280
...driver's license, Social Security.

1062
01:19:48,520 --> 01:19:49,480
You're shitting me.

1063
01:19:49,680 --> 01:19:52,960
If they trace any accounts,
they'll wind up chasing...

1064
01:19:53,120 --> 01:19:54,800
...a figment of my imagination.

1065
01:19:54,960 --> 01:19:56,880
Well, I'll be damned!

1066
01:19:58,160 --> 01:19:59,840
Did I say you were good?

1067
01:20:00,200 --> 01:20:01,760
Shit, you are Rembrandt.

1068
01:20:02,440 --> 01:20:04,120
The funny thing is...

1069
01:20:04,320 --> 01:20:08,240
...on the outside, I was an honest man,
straight as an arrow.

1070
01:20:08,640 --> 01:20:10,840
I had to come to prison to be a crook.

1071
01:20:19,360 --> 01:20:20,640
Ever bother you?

1072
01:20:22,040 --> 01:20:24,920
I don't run the scams.
I just process the profits.

1073
01:20:25,200 --> 01:20:27,120
A fine line, maybe...

1074
01:20:27,640 --> 01:20:29,640
...but I also built that library...

1075
01:20:29,840 --> 01:20:32,760
...and used it to help guys
get their high school diploma.

1076
01:20:32,960 --> 01:20:35,120
Why do you think
he lets me do all that?

1077
01:20:35,280 --> 01:20:37,400
Keep you happy and doing the laundry.

1078
01:20:37,600 --> 01:20:39,000
Money instead of sheets.

1079
01:20:39,360 --> 01:20:41,840
Well, I work cheap.
That's the tradeoff.

1080
01:20:58,400 --> 01:21:00,920
Tommy Williams
came to Shawshank in 1965...

1081
01:21:01,160 --> 01:21:03,280
...on a two-year stretch for B and E.

1082
01:21:03,520 --> 01:21:05,760
That's breaking and entering to you.

1083
01:21:06,040 --> 01:21:10,080
Cops caught him sneaking TV sets
out the back door of a JC Penney.

1084
01:21:10,520 --> 01:21:11,720
Young punk.

1085
01:21:11,920 --> 01:21:13,520
Mr. Rock 'n' Roll...

1086
01:21:13,680 --> 01:21:15,160
...cocky as hell.

1087
01:21:15,360 --> 01:21:17,640
Come on, old boys.
Moving like molasses!

1088
01:21:17,880 --> 01:21:19,560
Making me look bad.

1089
01:21:19,800 --> 01:21:21,480
We liked him immediately.

1090
01:21:21,720 --> 01:21:25,320
I'm backing out the door
and I got the TV like this.

1091
01:21:25,600 --> 01:21:29,080
A big old thing. I couldn't see shit.
Then I hear this voice.

1092
01:21:29,680 --> 01:21:31,560
"Freeze, kid, hands in the air."

1093
01:21:31,760 --> 01:21:36,040
I was standing there, holding onto
that TV. Finally the voice says:

1094
01:21:36,240 --> 01:21:39,880
"You hear what I said, boy?"
I say, "Yes, sir. I did.

1095
01:21:40,080 --> 01:21:43,440
But if I drop this, you get me
on destruction of property too."

1096
01:21:47,720 --> 01:21:49,920
You done some stretch
in Cashman, right?

1097
01:21:50,400 --> 01:21:54,200
Yeah, that was an easy piece of time,
let me tell you.

1098
01:21:54,480 --> 01:21:56,320
Weekend furloughs.
Work programs.

1099
01:21:56,520 --> 01:21:57,560
Not like here.

1100
01:21:57,720 --> 01:22:00,080
Sounds like you done time all over.

1101
01:22:00,480 --> 01:22:02,800
I've been in and out since I was 1 3.

1102
01:22:03,000 --> 01:22:05,080
Name it, chances are I've been there.

1103
01:22:05,280 --> 01:22:07,840
Perhaps you should try a new profession.

1104
01:22:09,200 --> 01:22:10,680
What I mean is...

1105
01:22:11,040 --> 01:22:14,360
...you're not a very good thief.
You should try something else.

1106
01:22:14,560 --> 01:22:17,640
Yeah, what the hell
you know about it, Capone?

1107
01:22:18,080 --> 01:22:19,560
What are you in for?

1108
01:22:19,840 --> 01:22:20,800
Me?

1109
01:22:23,120 --> 01:22:24,720
A lawyer fucked me.

1110
01:22:28,480 --> 01:22:31,320
Everybody's innocent in here.
Don't you know that?

1111
01:22:38,880 --> 01:22:43,160
As it turned out, Tommy had himself
a young wife and a new baby girl.

1112
01:22:43,680 --> 01:22:45,720
Maybe he thought of them
on the streets...

1113
01:22:45,920 --> 01:22:48,280
...or his child growing up
not knowing her daddy.

1114
01:22:48,600 --> 01:22:49,920
Whatever it was...

1115
01:22:50,240 --> 01:22:52,600
...something lit a fire
under that boy's ass.

1116
01:22:56,280 --> 01:22:59,000
Thought I might try for
my high school equivalency.

1117
01:22:59,200 --> 01:23:01,600
Hear you helped
a couple of fellas with that.

1118
01:23:02,920 --> 01:23:05,040
I don't waste time with losers, Tommy.

1119
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:08,760
I ain't no goddamn loser.

1120
01:23:10,480 --> 01:23:12,240
-You mean that?
-Yeah.

1121
01:23:13,840 --> 01:23:15,200
You really mean that?

1122
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:17,480
Yes, sir, I do.

1123
01:23:17,680 --> 01:23:19,600
Good. Because if we do this...

1124
01:23:19,800 --> 01:23:23,600
...we do it all the way,
a hundred percent, nothing half-assed.

1125
01:23:23,800 --> 01:23:25,560
Thing is, see...

1126
01:23:26,720 --> 01:23:28,240
...I don't read so good.

1127
01:23:29,320 --> 01:23:30,360
"Well."

1128
01:23:32,320 --> 01:23:34,000
You don't read...

1129
01:23:34,200 --> 01:23:35,680
...so well.

1130
01:23:37,920 --> 01:23:39,360
We'll get to that.

1131
01:23:43,600 --> 01:23:45,640
So Andy took Tommy under his wing.

1132
01:23:45,840 --> 01:23:48,360
Started walking him through his ABC's.

1133
01:23:50,440 --> 01:23:52,560
Tommy took to it pretty well too.

1134
01:23:52,800 --> 01:23:55,480
Boy found brains he never knew he had.

1135
01:23:57,680 --> 01:24:01,000
