but she's married to some other guy.

1211
01:28:21,840 --> 01:28:24,320
Some hotshot banker.

1212
01:28:25,680 --> 01:28:28,120
And he's the one they pinned it on.

1213
01:28:39,120 --> 01:28:42,840
I have to say that's
the most amazing story I ever heard.

1214
01:28:44,040 --> 01:28:46,440
What amazes me most
is you'd be taken in by it.

1215
01:28:47,120 --> 01:28:48,040
Sir?

1216
01:28:50,200 --> 01:28:53,640
It's obvious this fellow Williams
is impressed with you.

1217
01:28:54,240 --> 01:28:58,040
He hears your tale of woe
and naturally wants to cheer you up.

1218
01:28:58,200 --> 01:29:00,280
He's young, not terribly bright.

1219
01:29:00,800 --> 01:29:04,080
It's not surprising he wouldn't
know what a state he put you in.

1220
01:29:04,480 --> 01:29:05,960
Sir, he's telling the truth.

1221
01:29:06,720 --> 01:29:10,720
Let's say for the moment
this Blatch does exist.

1222
01:29:11,000 --> 01:29:15,400
You think he'd just fall to his knees
and cry, "Yes, I did it. I confess.

1223
01:29:15,640 --> 01:29:18,200
By the way,
add a life term to my sentence."

1224
01:29:18,400 --> 01:29:21,080
With Tommy's testimony,
I can get a new trial.

1225
01:29:21,280 --> 01:29:23,640
That's assuming Blatch is still there.

1226
01:29:23,880 --> 01:29:25,720
Chances are, he'd be released by now.

1227
01:29:25,920 --> 01:29:28,280
They'd have his last known address.

1228
01:29:28,480 --> 01:29:30,320
It's a chance, isn't it?

1229
01:29:32,600 --> 01:29:34,240
How can you be so obtuse?

1230
01:29:35,120 --> 01:29:36,080
What?

1231
01:29:37,520 --> 01:29:38,960
What did you call me?

1232
01:29:39,160 --> 01:29:40,800
Obtuse. Is it deliberate?

1233
01:29:41,160 --> 01:29:42,600
You're forgetting yourself.

1234
01:29:42,920 --> 01:29:45,760
The country club
will have his old timecards.

1235
01:29:45,920 --> 01:29:48,600
Records, W-2s with his name on them.

1236
01:29:48,760 --> 01:29:51,360
